ed%20directly%20over%20the%20wings%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepointsguy.co.uk%2F2017%2F10%2Fthe-truth-about-flight-turbulence%2F%5C%22%3Emost%20stable%20area%20of%20the%20plane%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20center%20of%20lift%2C%20so%20sitting%20here%C2%A0makes%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cntraveler.com%2Fstory%2Fwhere-to-sit-on-a-plane-to-prevent-motion-sickness%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520seat%2520directly%2520over%2520the%2Cthe%2520Aviation%2520Medicine%2520Advisory%2520Service.%5C%22%3Esmoothest%20ride%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20the%20plane%20hit%20turbulence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPossible%20downside%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20area%20tends%20to%20be%20a%20little%20noisier%20due%20to%20the%20location%20of%20the%20plane's%20engines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAny%20window%20seat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20window%20seat%20is%20my%20seat%20of%20choice.%20It%20provides%20beautiful%2C%20relaxing%20views%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20ideal%20distractions%20if%20you're%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-deal-with-travel-anxiety-2019-2%5C%22%3Enervous%20flyer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20won't%20be%20disturbed%20by%20other%20passengers%20when%20they%20get%20up%20and%20use%20the%20restroom.%C2%A0You're%20left%20alone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-to-sit-on-a-plane-to-sleep-2018-12%5C%22%3Eto%20sleep%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20can%20lean%20your%20head%20on%20the%20window%20pane%20while%20you%20do%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch1%3E%3Cstrong%3EWORST%20PLACES%20TO%20SIT%20ON%20A%20PLANE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh1%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224603%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20stock%20image%20of%20people%20sitting%20in%20seats%20on%20a%20plane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63503c492e2a8d0018d383f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223452%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConsider%20the%20section%20of%20the%20plane%20where%20you%20want%20to%20be%20seated%20before%20booking.%3Cp%3ECrist%C3%B3bal%20Alvarado%20Minic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ESeats%20directly%20in%20front%20or%20behind%20the%20bulkhead%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20you're%20behind%20the%20bulkhead%2C%20you%20usually%20have%20to%20put%20all%20of%20your%20belongings%20in%20the%20overhead%20compartment%20since%20there's%20no%20seat%20in%20front%20of%20you.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20no%20tray%20table%20to%20put%20down%20at%20your%20own%20convenience.%20Instead%2C%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20the%20crew%20for%20a%20table%20to%20slot%20into%20your%20seat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20also%20the%20spot%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhacks-traveling-with-a-baby-2018-9%5C%22%3Ebassinets%20are%20frequently%20placed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20if%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20hear%20kids%20crying%20during%20your%20flight%2C%20think%20twice%20about%20selecting%20a%20seat%20behind%20the%20bulkhead.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnother%20downside%20is%20that%20seats%20directly%20in%20front%20of%20a%20bulkhead%20don't%20recline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPossible%20perk%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20peeve%20about%20people%20reclining%20their%20seats%20into%20your%20space%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworst-people-to-sit-next-to-on-a-plane-2018-11%5C%22%3Epushing%20on%20your%20chair%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20time%20they%20use%20their%20tray%20table%2C%20then%20a%20seat%20behind%20or%20in%20front%20of%20the%20bulkhead%20is%20the%20one%20for%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeats%20near%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0the%20cabin%20restroom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYou'll%20also%20have%20other%20passengers%20hanging%20around%20you%20the%20entire%20flight%20as%20they%20wait%20for%20their%20turn%20to%20use%20the%20restroom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20escape%20the%20flushing%20noises%2C%20the%20bright%20lights%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20the%20smell%20of%20the%20restroom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPossible%20perk%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20may%20not%20have%20to%20wait%20in%20a%20queue%20for%20the%20toilet%20if%20you're%20in%20this%20seat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeats%20by%20the%20galley%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20galley%20is%20where%20the%20crew%C2%A0prepares%20all%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoods-airlines-dont-serve-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein-flight%20meals%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20refreshments.%20It's%20usually%20located%20at%20the%20front%20and%20back%20of%20the%20plane%2C%20but%20larger%20aircraft%C2%A0sometimes%20have%20one%20in%20the%20middle%20as%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEverything%20is%20stored%20in%20metal%20boxes%20and%20carts%2C%20so%20the%20area%20around%20the%20galley%20can%20be%20noisy.%20Plus%2C%20people%20usually%20chat%20there%2C%20which%20adds%20to%20the%20noise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%20least%20one%20crew%20member%20is%20on%20duty%20the%20whole%20flight%2C%20meaning%20the%20lights%20will%20be%20on%20the%20entire%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20especially%20recommend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-never-do-on-plane-flight-attendant-tips-2022-8%5C%22%3Eavoiding%20the%20aisle%20seat%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20galley%20unless%20you%20want%20people%20and%20carts%20bumping%20into%20your%20shoulders%20and%20shins%20the%20entire%20flight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERear%20section%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20back%20of%20the%20plane%20is%20definitely%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepointsguy.co.uk%2F2017%2F10%2Fthe-truth-about-flight-turbulence%2F%5C%22%3Eworst%20place%20to%20sit%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20travelers%20who%20hate%20turbulence%20since%20it's%20far%20from%20the%20plane's%20center%20of%20lift%20and%20gravity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20section%20can%20also%20be%20very%20loud%20since%20some%20planes%20have%20engines%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flyingmag.com%2Fhow-an-auxiliary-power-unit-works%2F%5C%22%3Eauxiliary%20power%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20toward%20the%20back%20of%20the%20body%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsimpleflying.com%2Faircraft-noise-sources-reduction-measures%2F%5C%22%3Emake%20a%20lot%20of%20noise%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAny%20middle%20seat%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPersonally%2C%20I%20think%20the%20middle%20seat%20is%20the%20worst%20you%20can%20have%20on%20a%20plane%2C%20especially%20for%20a%20solo%20traveler.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EToo%20often%2C%20the%20people%20in%20the%20window%20and%20aisle%20seats%20take%20up%20the%20entire%20row's%20armrests%2C%20leaving%20the%20person%20in%20the%20middle%20to%20awkwardly%20cross%20their%20arms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere%2C%20you're%20either%20going%20to%20be%20disturbed%20by%20the%20person%20in%20the%20window%20seat%20when%20they%20want%20to%20use%20the%20restroom%2C%20or%20you'll%20have%20to%20interrupt%20the%20person%20in%20the%20aisle%20seat%20to%20use%20it%20yourself.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGood%20luck%20trying%20to%20sleep%20unless%20you're%20happy%20to%20nod%20off%20onto%20someone%20else's%20shoulder.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20October%2019%2C%202022%2C%20and%20most%20recently%20updated%20on%20August%2028%2C%202024.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-is-the-best-place-to-sit-on-plane-worst-seats%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725374864000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.