tration%20has%20also%20actively%20sought%20to%20impede%20the%20country's%20rapidly%20growing%20semiconductor%20or%20microchip%20industry.%20This%20has%20triggered%20a%20chip%20war%20between%20the%20world's%20two%20biggest%20economies.%20The%20US%20wants%20to%20regain%20its%20leadership%20role%20in%20the%20semiconductor%20ecosystem%2C%20while%20China%20wants%20to%20become%20self-reliant%20to%20propel%20its%20economy%20to%20be%20the%20world's%20number%20one.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20conflict%20is%20the%20recognition%20that%20semiconductors%20are%20essential%20not%20just%20for%20consumer%20electronics%20but%20also%20for%20advanced%20technologies%2C%20including%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20quantum%20computing%20and%20military%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20worry%20for%20the%20US%20that%20its%20containment%20policy%20against%20China%20has%20not%20had%20the%20desired%20effect.%20It%20invokes%20national%20security%20as%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20reasons%20for%20checkmating%20the%20Chinese%20chipmaking%20industry's%20rapid%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20decades%20ago%2C%20China%20lagged%20far%20behind%20the%20US%20in%20the%20chip%20industry%20by%20several%20generations.%20But%20American%20policymakers%20overlooked%20China's%20eagerness%20to%20flex%20its%20muscles%20in%20the%20microchips%20industry%20for%20long.%20Today%2C%20there%20is%20a%20global%20consensus%20among%20experts%20that%20Chinese%20companies%20are%20behind%20the%20world's%20most%20advanced%20chip-making%20companies%20by%20only%20three%20to%20five%20years.%20For%20microchips%2C%20this%20gap%20is%20too%20narrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20Containing%20China%20Isn't%20Easy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20preserve%20its%20technological%20supremacy%20and%20national%20security%2C%20the%20US%20has%20imposed%20stringent%20export%20controls%20on%20semiconductor%20technology%20to%20China%2C%20aiming%20to%20limit%20the%20latter's%20ability%20to%20manufacture%20advanced%20chips.%20This%20strategy%20has%20been%20bolstered%20by%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20support%20domestic%20chip%20manufacturing%2C%20mandated%20in%20the%20CHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act%2C%20which%20allocates%20substantial%20funds%20to%20boost%20American%20semiconductor%20production%20and%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20containing%20China%20is%20proving%20to%20be%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%2C%3Cem%3E%20The%20Asian%2021st%20Century%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Kishore%20Mahbubani%2C%20a%20former%20diplomat%20who%20served%20as%20Singapore's%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20has%20challenged%20the%20US%20policy%20of%20containing%20China's%20rise%20and%20said%20it%20would%20prove%20counter-productive.%20He%20argues%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20make%20a%20prediction%20confidently%20that%20the%20containment%20policy%20will%20fail%2C%20because%20China%20has%20already%20integrated%20itself%20with%20the%20world%2C%20more%20than%20the%20US%20has.%20More%20countries%20do%20trade%20with%20China%20than%20they%20do%20with%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Are%20Semiconductors%20So%20Important%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20economic%20historian%20Chris%20Miller%20captured%20the%20microchip%20industry's%20growing%20importance%20in%20his%20aptly%20titled%20book%2C%20Chip%20War.%20One%20of%20Barack%20Obama's%20favourite%20books%2C%20it%20reads%20like%20a%20non-fiction%20thriller.%20Miller%20explains%20how%20semiconductors%20came%20to%20play%20a%20critical%20role%20in%20modern%20life%20and%20how%20the%20US%20became%20dominant%20in%20chip%20design%20and%20manufacturing%20and%20applied%20this%20technology%20to%20military%20systems.%20%26quot%3BToday%2C%20military%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20geopolitical%20power%20are%20built%20on%20a%20foundation%20of%20computer%20chips.%20Virtually%20everything-from%20missiles%20to%20microwaves-runs%20on%20chips%2C%20including%20cars%2C%20smartphones%2C%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20even%20the%20electric%20grid.%20Until%20recently%2C%20America%20designed%20and%20built%20the%20fastest%20chips%20and%20maintained%20its%20lead%20as%20the%20%231%20superpower%2C%20but%20America's%20edge%20is%20in%20danger%20of%20slipping%2C%20undermined%20by%20players%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20Korea%2C%20and%20Europe%20taking%20over%20manufacturing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20the%20book%20reveals%2C%20China%2C%20which%20spends%20more%20on%20chips%20than%20any%20other%20product%2C%20is%20pouring%20billions%20into%20a%20chip-building%20initiative%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20US.%20At%20stake%20is%20America's%20military%20superiority%20and%20economic%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Big%20Is%20The%20Industry%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMicrochips%20are%20used%20in%20nearly%20every%20digital%20gadget%20or%20machine%20we%20use%20today%2C%20ranging%20from%20computers%20to%20smartphones%2C%20from%20aircraft%20to%20military%20equipment%2C%20from%20drones%20to%20medical%20equipment%20to%20AI%20tools.%20The%20car%20we%20drive%20has%2C%20on%20average%2C%201%2C500%20chips%3B%20the%20smartphone%20we%20use%20is%20powered%20by%20two-three%20dozen%20microchips.%20Miller%20says%20it's%20a%20new%20oil%2C%20and%20like%20the%20oil%2C%20the%20semiconductor%20industry%20is%20also%20being%20dominated%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20giant%20of%20an%20industry.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20World%20Semiconductor%20Trade%20Statistics%20(WSTS)%20raised%20its%20forecast%20for%20the%20year-on-year%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20global%20semiconductor%20market%20this%20year%20to%2016%25.%20The%20global%20semiconductor%20market%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WSTS%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20%24611.2%20billion%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESemiconductor%20manufacturing%20comprises%20four%20elements%3A%20design%2C%20lithography%2C%20fabrication%2C%20assembly%2C%20and%20packaging.%20There%20are%20different%20types%20of%20advanced%20chips%2C%20but%20the%20four%20primary%20types%20are%20logic%20chips%2C%20memory%20chips%2C%20and%20analogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20manufacturing%20technology%2C%20advanced%20or%20cutting-edge%20microchips%20are%205%20nm%20or%20even%202%20nm%20in%20size.%20In%20contrast%2C%20legacy%20chips%20refer%20to%20those%20which%20are%2028%20nm%20or%20bigger.%20But%20these%20legacy%20chips%20are%20not%20to%20be%20sniggered%20at.%20They%20are%20widely%20used%20in%20various%20applications%2C%20including%20automobiles%2C%20medical%20devices%2C%20household%20appliances%2C%20energy%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20aerospace%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETypes%20Of%20Chips%2C%20And%20Their%20Lead%20Manufacturers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMicrochips%20can%20broadly%20be%20divided%20into%20logic%20and%20memory%20chips.%20South%20Korea%20specialises%20in%20memory%20chips%2C%20such%20as%20DRAM%20and%20NAND%20flash%2C%20which%20are%20used%20for%20data%20storage.%20Its%20companies%20Samsung%20Electronics%20and%20SK%20Hynix%20are%20among%20the%20world's%20largest%20producers%20of%20memory%20chips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Taiwan%20specialises%20in%20logic%20chips%20(also%20known%20as%20processors%20or%20central%20processing%20units%20(CPUs)%2C%20which%20are%20used%20for%20computing%20and%20data%20processing.%20The%20Taiwan%20Semiconductor%20Manufacturing%20Company%20(TSMC)%20produces%20an%20estimated%2090%25%20of%20the%20world's%20super-advanced%20semiconductor%20chips.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20not%20forget%20China%20entertains%20sovereignty%20claims%20over%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20governments%20in%20the%20West%20fear%20that%20Beijing%20will%20soon%20take%20control%20of%20it.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20the%20semiconductor%20global%20supply%20chain%20will%20be%20massively%20disrupted.%20But%20more%20than%20that%2C%20what%20the%20US%20fears%20is%20that%20China%20will%20become%20the%20dominant%20player%20in%20logic%20chips%2C%20without%20which%20computers%20don't%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20China%20Overtook%20US%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20invented%20semiconductors%20in%20the%20early%201950s%20and%20remained%20the%20world's%20leading%20chip%20builder%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20But%20between%201990-2021%2C%20its%20share%20of%20global%20semiconductor%20production%20fell%20from%2037%25%20to%2012%25.%20In%20the%20same%20period%2C%20China's%20share%20leapt%20up%20from%20almost%20nothing%20to%2015%25.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20decided%20to%20revive%20its%20pre-eminent%20position%2C%20and%20the%20result%20was%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20CHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act%20of%202022.%20Heavy%20subsidies%20are%20being%20given%20to%20chip%20manufacturers%2C%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20Act%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20fair%20trade%20practices%20as%20it%20required%20subsidy%20recipients%20not%20to%20invest%20in%20Chinese%20semiconductor%20production%20of%20advanced%20chips.%20China%20protested%2C%20but%20moved%20on.%20In%20response%2C%20it%20has%20now%20embarked%20on%20an%20ambitious%20initiative%20to%20achieve%20self-reliance%20in%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%2C%20recognising%20that%20its%20dependence%20on%20foreign%20technology%20poses%20a%20significant%20vulnerability.%20Interestingly%2C%20in%20June%202023%2C%20the%20US%20had%20also%20brokered%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20Netherlands%20to%20restrict%20its%20exports%20to%20China%20of%20leading-edge%20EUV%20(extreme%20ultraviolet)%20equipment%2C%20a%20new%20technology%20used%20to%20manufacture%20the%20most%20intricate%20layers%20on%20a%20chip.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Global%20Battleground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chip%20war%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20bilateral%20tug%20of%20war%20but%20a%20global%20contest%20involving%20various%20key%20players%2C%20who%20are%20all%20trying%20to%20navigate%20the%20complex%20interplay%20of%20technology%2C%20security%2C%20and%20economic%20interests.%20The%20war%20is%20not%20coming%20to%20an%20end%20anytime%20soon%2C%20with%20both%20parties%20unwilling%20to%20collaborate%20for%20greater%20global%20good.%20The%20US%20is%20still%20in%20control%2C%20but%20China%20is%20eating%20away%20at%20its%20tech%20supremacy%2C%20chip%20by%20chip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20where%20does%20India%20stand%3F%20Has%20India%20joined%20the%20race%3F%20Can%20India%20facilitate%20a%20dynamic%20microchip%20landscape%3F%20The%20second%20part%20of%20this%20column%20will%20try%20to%20answer%20these%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725371340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fkvno5uf8_us-china_625x300_03_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fchina-is-eating-away-at-uss-tech-reign-chip-by-chip-6481939%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20worry%20for%20the%20US%20that%20its%20containment%20policy%20against%20China%20has%20not%20had%20the%20desired%20effect.%20It%20invokes%20national%20security%20as%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20reasons%20for%20checkmating%20the%20Chinese%20chipmaking%20industry's%20rapid%20growth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fchina-is-eating-away-at-uss-tech-reign-chip-by-chip-6481939%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LIVE%20news%3A%20Foreign%20direct%20investment%20in%20India%20jumps%2047.8%