wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBringing%20different%20nationalities%20together%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIris%2C%20an%20art%20and%20design%20student%20from%20France%2C%20had%20come%20to%20India%20in%20the%201990s%20for%20her%20diploma%20project%20as%20part%20of%20her%20final%20year%20assignment%20of%20art%20school.%20She%20started%20coming%20to%20India%20to%20work%20with%20various%20non-profit%20organisations%20to%20train%20Indian%20artisans%20in%20making%20products%20that%20could%20be%20sold%20in%20the%20international%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20permanently%20settled%20in%20India%20in%202006%20after%20her%20marriage%20to%20Bishwadeep%2C%20a%20former%20journalist%2C%20whom%20she%20met%20at%20a%20yoga%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIris%20continued%20to%20work%20as%20a%20design%20consultant%20with%20international%20clothing%20brands.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20she%20was%20struck%20by%20the%20massive%20amounts%20of%20fabric%20waste%20generated%20by%20the%20fashion%20industry%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShe%20used%20to%20visit%20many%20of%20these%20factories%20in%20Delhi%2C%20which%20is%20a%20big%20production%20hub%20for%20many%20international%20fashion%20brands.%20She%20discovered%20that%20fabric%20waste%20is%20discarded%20in%20extreme%20bulk%20quantities.%20It%20was%20here%20that%20she%20was%20struck%20with%20the%20idea%20to%20use%20the%20scraps%20for%20making%20a%20useful%20product%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Bishwadeep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20she%20was%20already%20training%20artisan%20groups%2C%20she%20came%20across%20a%20marginalised%20group%20of%20Afghan%20refugee%20women.%20The%20refugee%20issue%20was%20close%20to%20her%20heart.%20We%20thought%20that%20this%20could%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20as%20it%20was%20difficult%20for%20us%20also%20to%20tap%20into%20the%20talents%20of%20artisans%20who%20live%20in%20far%20off%20tribal%20villages.%20We%20decided%20to%20marry%20both%20the%20concepts%20of%20upcycling%20fabric%20waste%20and%20generating%20employment%20for%20refugee%20women%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20bid%20to%20do%20something%20meaningful%2C%20Bishwadeep%20quit%20his%20job%20as%20an%20executive%20editor%20at%20Outlook%20news%20magazine%20and%20co-founded%20SilaiWali%20along%20with%20his%20wife.%20%E2%80%9CJournalism%20allowed%20me%20a%20way%20to%20work%20for%20society%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20differently%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20of%20service%20to%20society%20in%20a%20direct%20way.%20I%20was%20motivated%20by%20my%20wife%20to%20work%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20couple%20decided%20to%20start%20SilaiWali%20in%202018%20for%20financial%20independence%20of%20Afghan%20women%20refugees%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Currently%2C%20Iris%20and%20Bishwadeep%20are%20providing%20a%20livelihood%20to%20more%20than%2070%20Afghan%20refugee%20women.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-2-1725019714-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-363652%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECurrently%2C%20Iris%20and%20Bishwadeep%20are%20providing%20a%20livelihood%20to%20more%20than%2070%20Afghan%20refugee%20women.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECatering%20to%20150%20cities%20worldwide%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20company%2C%20Bishwadeep%20shares%20that%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F299084%2Fdesigner-upcycles-scrap-fabric-into-trendy-clothes-bags-lets-save-as-anshika-yadav%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaste%20fabric%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20sourced%20from%20garment%20factories%2C%20it%20is%20sorted%2C%20cut%2C%20and%20transformed%20by%20these%20refugee%20artisans%20into%20dolls%20and%20other%20home%20decor%20items%3B%20incorporating%20traditional%20embroidery%2C%20sewing%2C%20and%20crocheting%20techniques.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20handcrafted%20dolls%20reflect%20the%20personalities%20and%20stories%20of%20the%20artisans%2C%20making%20each%20creation%20a%20symbol%20of%20resilience%20and%20creativity.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20all%20handwork%20and%20each%20doll%20reflects%20the%20unique%20personalities%20of%20the%20artisan%20who%20crafted%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESilaiWali%20participates%20in%20trade%20shows%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Paris%2C%20boosting%20its%20presence%20in%20the%20global%20market.%20With%20this%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20been%20able%20to%20tap%20into%20a%20growing%20demand%20for%20these%20dolls%20in%20150%20cities%20worldwide%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20Japan%2C%20Korea%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Australia%2C%20and%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20Jaipur%2C%20Chennai%2C%20and%20Goa%20within%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCfA9pX3DaB2%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCfA9pX3DaB2%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCfA9pX3DaB2%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Silaiwali%20(%40silaiwali)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20handcrafted%20items%20by%20SilaiWali%20range%20from%20Rs%20820%20to%20Rs%205400.%20The%20brand%20exports%20goods%20worth%20%24200%2C000%20every%20year%2C%20with%20peak%20seasons%20around%20September%20to%20December%20to%20cater%20to%20Christmas%20and%20Halloween%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20SilaiWali%20claims%20to%20have%20trained%20and%20reskilled%20325%20women%20refugees.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20one%20point%2C%20we%20had%20150%20such%20women%20working%20with%20us.%20But%20most%20of%20them%20migrated%20to%20Canada%20due%20to%20changing%20immigration%20policies%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Bishwadeep.%20Despite%20facing%20such%20challenges%2C%20SilaiWali%20continues%20to%20make%20a%20significant%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20wages%20of%20the%20artisans%2C%20Bishwadeep%20says%20it%20is%20calculated%20following%20the%20wage%20ladder%20mandated%20by%20the%20World%20Fair%20Trade%20Organisation.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20incomes%20vary%20from%20artisan%20to%20artisan%2C%20they%20earn%20between%20Rs%2012%2C000%20to%20Rs%2014%2C000%20every%20month.%20It%20can%20also%20increase%20depending%20on%20factors%20like%20sales%20and%20special%20orders%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20her%20experience%20of%20working%20with%20these%20women%2C%20Iris%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAfghan%20women%20have%20a%20pleasant%20demeanour.%20They%20are%20very%20proud%20of%20their%20heritage.%20They%20listen%20to%20my%20instructions%20and%20are%20not%20afraid%20to%20disagree%20with%20me%20when%20necessary.%20They%20have%20shown%20amazing%20resilience%20in%20rebuilding%20their%20lives%20in%20India%2C%20however%20temporary%20their%20current%20residence%20may%20be.%20Many%20SilaiWali%20women%20have%20broken%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20by%20being%20the%20sole-earning%20members%20of%20their%20families.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20these%20families%20were%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20Their%20children%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20sent%20to%20school.%20We%20are%20glad%20that%20our%20intervention%20has%20somewhat%20eased%20their%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Iris%2C%20who%20finds%20this%20work%20extremely%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20at%20his%20decision%20to%20quit%20journalism%20to%20establish%20a%20career%20in%20the%20social%20enterprise%20sector%2C%20Bishwadeep%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20do%20impacts%20so%20many%20families%20and%20provides%20them%20with%20dignity%2C%20spending%20power%2C%20demolishing%20the%20patriarchal%20system%2C%20and%20creating%20an%20impact%20that%20can%20be%20seen%20on%20the%20ground.%20This%20work%20gave%20me%20an%20opportunity%20to%20directly%20engage%20with%20the%20marginalised%20sections%20at%20the%20grassroots.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%20All%20photos%3A%20SilaiWali%20social%20verticals.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725030423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSilaiWali-1-1725019598.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D363502%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iris%20Strill%20and%20Bishwadeep%20Moitra%20founded%20SilaiWali%2C%20a%20social%20enterprise%20in%20India%20that%20empowers%20Afghan%20refugee%20women%20by%20helping%20them%20turn%20waste%20fabric%20into%20handcrafted%20rag%20dolls.%20Through%20this%2C%20they%20have%20also%20diverted%20around%2015%2C000%20kg%20of%20fabric%20from%20landfills%20so%20far.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20This%20Startup%E2%80%99s%20Innovation%20Can%20Save%20Over%203000%20Kg%20Of%20Paper%20Waste%20From%20Reaching%20Landfills%20Every%20Month%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20was%20a%20tough%20time%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20including%20businesses.%20The%20situation%20was%20bleak%20at%20Chikkamagaluru%20too%2C%20at%20BG%20Boutique%20Paper%20Mills%20Private%20Limited.%20BG%20Seetharaman%2C%20Founder%20and%20Managing%20Director%20of%20the%20company%2C%20faced%20a%20tough%20time%20in%20keeping%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F348979%2Fcotton-waste-from-factories-sustainable-stationery-rashi-agarwal-roohani-rang-recycled-diary-notebooks-support-artisans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehandmade%20paper%20company%20%3C%2Fa%3Erunning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPassionate%20about%20sustainability%20and%20preventing%20agricultural%20and%20plastic%20waste%20from%20entering%20the%20landfills%2C%20he%20used%20the%20time%20to%20brainstorm%20ideas%20to%20work%20on%20his%20dream%20project%20which%20was%20an-end-to-end%20solution%20that%20would%20prevent%20solid%20wastes%20from%20entering%20landfills.%20But%20how%20could%20that%20be%20done%3F%20By%20developing%20a%20machine%20that%20recycles%20waste%20at%20source.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20discussed%20this%20idea%20with%20Vinay%20Kumar%2C%20a%20social%20entrepreneur%2C%20and%20Rajeeva%20Deekshit%2C%20a%20green%20chemical%20expert%2C%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months.%20They%20came%20to%20a%20conclusion%20that%20the%20two%20areas%20they%20wanted%20to%20target%20were%20waste%20paper%20and%20fibrous%20agricultural%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20according%20to%20the%20founders%20is%20that%2C%20about%2030%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20paper%20is%20getting%20into%20the%20landfills%20due%20to%20being%20coated%20with%20plastic%20or%20aluminium%20and%20are%20contaminated%20with%20beverages%20that%20makes%20it%20unsuitable%20for%20recycling.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20almost%2087%20million%20tonnes%20of%20crop%20residue%20is%20burned%20annually%20in%20India%2C%20as%20per%20a%20Science%20Direct%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22B%20G%20Seetharaman%2C%20Vinay%20Kumar%20and%20Rajeeva%20Deekshit%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-363693%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EB%20G%20Seetharaman%2C%20Vinay%20Kumar%2C%20and%20Rajeeva%20Deekshit%20(L-R)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20this%2C%20the%20trio%20started%20Indic%20Initiatives%20in%20July%202022%20and%20have%20developed%20a%20one%20of%20its%20kind%20waste%20paper%20recycler%20that%20tackles%20the%20difficult%20to%20recycle%20paper%20cups%2C%20label%20release%20paper%2C%20tissue%20papers%20and%20tetrapaks.%20Their%20machine%20recycles%20this%20waste%20into%20pulp%20boards%2C%20which%20can%20be%20further%20used%20to%20manufacture%20paper%20and%20moulded%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncubated%20at%20NSRCEL%20(IIM%20Bangalore)%20and%20IIMV%20FIELD%20(IIM%20Visakhapatnam)%2C%20the%20startup%20is%20planning%20to%20patent%20the%20machine%E2%80%99s%20design%20and%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETackling%20the%20difficult%20to%20recycle%20plastics%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mechanical%20engineer%20from%20BITS%20Pilani%2C%20Seetharaman%20also%20pursued%20research%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20in%20Bengaluru.%20After%20working%20at%20Seshasayee%20Paper%20and%20Boards%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20he%20set%20up%20his%20own%20handmade%20paper%20unit%20in%201997%2C%20called%20BG%20Boutique%20Paper%20Mills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Recycling%20paper%20cups%20at%20source!%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic1-1725015497-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-363603%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERecycling%20paper%20cups%20at%20source!%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20he%20claims%20that%20they%20make%20100%20percent%20recycled%20paper%2C%20paper%20bags%20and%20stationery%20from%20jute%20and%20cotton%20waste.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20built%20a%20semi-automatic%20machine%20in%202014%20as%20a%20ready-made%20paper%20machine%20was%20not%20available%20to%20our%20size%2C%20to%20process%20say%20100-200%20kg%20per%20day.%20We%20designed%20it%20to%20make%20paper%20from%20raw%20materials%20like%20jute%20waste%2C%20leather%20waste%2C%20banana%20waste%20and%20other%20unique%20raw%20materials%2C%E2%80%9D%20Seetharaman%20shares%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20cost%20of%20production%20was%20high%2C%20the%20first%20lockdown%20in%202020%20caused%20a%20huge%20roadblock.%20Now%2C%20the%20engineer%20and%20scientist%20thought%20of%20developing%20a%20complete%20product%20which%20could%20recycle%20paper%20waste%20at%20source.%20He%20calls%20it%20an%20%E2%80%98end-to-end%20paper%20machine%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20lay%20in%20building%20technology%20which%20would%20recover%20clean%20plastic%2C%20by%20removing%20silicone%20coatings%2C%20hazardous%20substances%20and%20beverage%20stains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeetharaman%20had%20already%20worked%20with%20Rajeeva%20in%202017%20to%20create%20a%20technology%20that%20removed%20glassine%20from%20label%20release%20papers.Their%20technology%20could%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F359436%2Fgrow-your-microgreens-using-this-portable-chemical-free-cultivator-made-of-banana-pulp-waste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecycle%20this%20silicone%20coated%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLabel%20release%20papers%20have%20a%20silicone%20coating%20which%20is%20hazardous%20and%20not%20recyclable.%20A%20big%20manufacturer%20had%20approached%20us%20to%20develop%20a%20technology%20to%20remove%20the%20coating%20and%20recover%20pulp.%20I%20knew%20that%20we%20could%20use%20the%20same%20technology%20for%20paper%20cups%20and%20tetra%20packs%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Seetharaman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20machine%20developed%20by%20Indic%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558.jpeg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558-300x226.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558-500x376.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558-768x578.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558-1536x1156.jpeg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Findic2-min-1725015558-150x113.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-363604%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221204%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20machine%20developed%20by%20Indic%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETetra%20packs%20too%20come%20coated%20with%20plastic%20or%20aluminium%20and%20are%20usually%20contaminated%20with%20beverages%2C%20tissue%20paper%2C%20and%20label%20release%20paper.%20Due%20to%20these%20complications%2C%20tetra%20packs%20and%20paper%20cups%20are%20not%20generally%20recycled%2C%20opines%20Seetharaman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20found%20that%20they%20are%20getting%20recycled%20efficiently%20because%20of%20their%20layers%20of%20plastic%20and%20aluminium.%20Separation%20of%20these%20layers%20is%20not%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20grants%20and%20awards%20after%20winning%20ELEVATE%20Karnataka%202023%20and%20Nidhi%20Prayas%202023%2C%20they%20built%20a%20pilot%20plant%20in%20Chikkamagaluru%2C%20where%20they%20were%20able%20to%20efficiently%20separate%20plastic%20from%20the%20paper%20cups%20and%20silicone%20gum%20from%20silicone%20coated%20paper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20they%20have%20a%20proof%20of%20concept%20at%20the%20minimum%20viable%20product%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20unit%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F351690%2Fyash-dayal-sharma-fertile-beeghas-organic-waste-vermicompost-stubble-burning-train-farmers-soil-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecover%20clean%20plastic%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20aluminium%20coatings%20for%20reuse%2C%20recover%20hazardous%20ink%20waste%20for%20reuse%20and%20upcycled%20fibrous%20agricultural%20wastes%20to%20create%20paper%20pulp%20that%20can%20be%20made%20into%20high-strength%20paper%20used%20for%20packaging%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vinay%2C%20Founder%20of%20Indic%20Initiatives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chartered%20accountant%20by%20education%2C%20Vinay%20is%20a%20social%20entrepreneur%20based%20in%20Bengaluru%20who%20started%20Indic%20to%20provide%20a%20platform%20for%20indigenous%20innovations%20that%20will%20benefit%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20machine%20works%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FTransformation-gif-1-1725015809.gif%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-363610%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20paper%20cups%2C%20tetra%20packs%20or%20tissues%20are%20received%2C%20they%20are%20manually%20put%20inside%20the%20recycling%20machine.%20The%20components%20go%20through%20a%20three-stage%20process.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20tetra%20packs%2C%20the%20machine%20uses%20a%20chemical%20suspension%20to%20separate%20it%20into%20aluminium%2C%20plastic%20and%20pulp.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20paper%20cups%2C%20it%20is%20separated%20into%20plastic%20and%20pulp.%20The%20pulp%20is%20then%20converted%20into%20pulp%20boards%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Seetharaman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20pulp%20boards%20are%20sold%20as%20raw%20materials%20for%20paper%20making%20or%20making%20moulded%20products.%20The%20aluminium%20and%20paper%20waste%20is%20sorted%20separately%20and%20given%20to%20recyclers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajeeva%20states%20that%20they%20developed%20an%20eco-friendly%20solution%20which%20separates%20these%20aluminium%2C%20silicone%20and%20plastic%20from%20tetra%20packs%20and%20paper%20cups%20respectively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20unique%20aspect%20about%20the%20machine%2C%20says%20Seetharaman%2C%20is%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20effluents%20released%20by%20the%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20in%20the%20paper%20and%20agriculture%20machines%2C%20we%20have%20ensured%20that%20there%20is%20no%20effluent%20released.%20Even%20in%20the%20case%20of%20banana%20waste%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20extracting%20the%20sap%20and%20using%20it%20as%20a%20liquid%20fertiliser.%20It%20will%20be%20a%20zero%20liquid%20discharge%20arrangement%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fembed%2Ffeed%2Fupdate%2Furn%3Ali%3AugcPost%3A7155481472135520257%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Embedded%20post%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22796%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20machine%20is%20designed%20for%20villages%2C%20malls%2C%20airports%20and%20more.%20It%20comes%20with%20a%20capacity%20of%20recycling%2050%20kg%20of%20paper%20waste%20per%20day%2C%20which%20can%20be%20extended%20to%20150%20kg.%20A%20larger%20machine%20which%20can%20process%20up%20to%20one%20tonne%20is%20also%20available.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20they%20are%20in%20talks%20with%20some%20village%20panchayats%20and%20malls%20in%20Karnataka%20and%20hope%20to%20launch%20soon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTransportation%20of%20paper%20waste%20for%20recycling%20to%20bigger%20plants%20is%20difficult%20and%20usually%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%20To%20prevent%20this%2C%20we%20must%20provide%20options%20to%20recycle%20at%20source.%20We%20want%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20waste%20generated%20is%20converted%20to%20good%20quality%20pulp%20boards.%20We%20will%20facilitate%20a%20buyback%20model%20for%20the%20pulp%20and%20send%20it%20to%20a%20paper%20mill%20or%20moulded%20product%20unit%20to%20close%20the%20loop%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Seetharaman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20piece%20of%20waste%2C%20be%20it%20plastic%20or%20paper%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F339831%2Fjamshedpur-rajiv-sharma-alve-smart-air-fresheners-plastic-free-eco-friendly-temple-flower-waste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20sent%20to%20the%20landfills%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%2C%20Images%20Courtesy%20BG%20Seetharaman%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725026390000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FCopy-of-Cover-image-58-1725024679.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3